==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic; cognate with Old Saxon ''[[megin]]'', Old High German ''[[magan]]'', Old Norse ''[[magn]]''

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈmæjen/}}

===Noun===
'''mæġen''' {{n}} (plural '''[[mægnu|mæġnu]]''')

# [[strength]], [[power]]
#:''Ðæt mycle mægen minra handa.''  The mighty power of my hands.
# [[force]], [[army]]
#:''Sibbe no wolde wið manna hwone mægenes Deniga.''  He wanted no peace with any man of the Danish forces.  (''Beowulf'', ll. 154-5)

